AH-Vest, Mercantile Bank, Reunert May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-06-30T22:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/ah-vest-mercantile-reunert-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose for a fifth day
advancing 138.24, or 0.44 percent, to 31,864.54 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg. The index retreated 2.2 percent last
month.  AH-Vest Ltd. (AHL)  : The food manufacturer reported a
loss of 2.45 million rand ($362,000) for the year to March, from
a profit of 1.15 million a year earlier. Shares were unchanged
at 20 cents.  Mercantile Bank Holdings Ltd. (MTL)  : The lender
controlled by Portugal’s Caixa Geral de Depositos SA released a
voluntary business update after arranging 50 million euros ($73
million) of funding from the World Bank’s International Finance
Corp. At the market close, the bank also said it had received an
unsolicited takeover offer from The Bidvest Group Ltd. The stock
closed at its highest in a month, surging 5 cents, or 25
percent, to 25 cents.  Reunert Ltd. (RLO)  : The maker of electric power cables
and telecommunications equipment holds its  annual general
meeting . Shares closed 62 cents, or 1 percent lower, at 61.13
rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
